This paper deals with the extraction of Creative Procedural Knowledge (CPK) from web design tutorials. It involves the use of machine learning models for text classification and sequence-to-sequence models. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
